concepts.term: this is the type of wave we use - the longitudinal wave traveling through soft tissue

evidence: In ultrasound, this is the type of wave we use - the longitudinal wave traveling through soft tissue.
In a longitudinal wave, the vibration and propagation directions are the same, while in a transverse wave, they are orthogonal. Both are just different ways energy can propagate through a medium.
